projects.description:
The project will contribute to efforts by the Government of Sri Lanka to increase employability of Sri Lankan aspiring migrant workers, ensuring a gender-sensitive, rights-sensitive approach. The project aims to result in the following;
1. The Government of Sri Lanka sustainably institutionalizes an Integrated Guidance and Referral System (IGRS) to promote skills development amongst aspiring migrant workers in a demand-driven manner.

Multiyear Project: Start date: 12/1/2022
